HEADWORD: Chylopoetic
<hw>Chy`lo*po*et"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chylopoiei^n</grk> to make into juice, <grk>chylo`s</grk> juice,
chyle + <grk>poiei^n</grk> to make.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Concerned in the formation of chyle; <as>as, the
<ex>chylopoetic</ex> organs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chylous</ent>⟦br⟧
